solution.approach:
Let pos1 be the 0‑based index of element 1 and posN be the 0‑based index of element N. We need to move 1 to index 0 (cost = pos1 swaps) and N to index N‑1 (cost = (N‑1‑posN) swaps). If pos1 < posN the two movements are independent, so the answer is pos1 + (N‑1‑posN). If pos1 > posN, moving N first shifts 1 one position left, reducing the total by one. Hence the answer is pos1 + (N‑1‑posN) – 1. The formula can be written compactly as:
    answer = pos1 + (N - 1 - posN) - (pos1 > posN ? 1 : 0);
The algorithm scans the array once to find pos1 and posN, then applies the formula. This runs in O(N) time per test case and O(1) extra space.

